.TH "bnx2x_func_reset_cmn" 9 "bnx2x_func_reset_cmn" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bnx2x_func_reset_cmn \- reset HW at common stage
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bnx2x_func_reset_cmn
.BI "(struct bnx2x *bp "  ","
.BI "const struct bnx2x_func_sp_drv_ops *drv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bp" 12
device handle
.IP "drv" 12
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reset HW at FW_MSG_CODE_DRV_UNLOAD_COMMON and
FW_MSG_CODE_DRV_UNLOAD_COMMON_CHIP stages: reset COMMON,
COMMON_CHIP, FUNCTION-only and PORT-only HW blocks.
